Bat populations in Scotland and the United Kingdom have declined considerably over the past century.
They are under threat because of the construction and development that affects their nests and the loss of their habitat.
Wind turbines and electrical wiring can also pose a risk to them, as can insecticidal papers and other chemical treatments of building materials or attacks from domestic cats.
