U.S.-China trade war could benefit Beijing
The first salvoes of the U.S.-China trade war were deafening, and while much remains to be done, a split between the countries could benefit Beijing, experts say.
U.S. President Donald Trump issued the first warning earlier this year by putting tariffs on major Chinese exports, such as solar panels, steel and aluminum.
