Now he passes the torch to his compatriot John Rahm, who already defeated American golf legend Tiger Woods by 2-1 in a singles match on Sunday.
“I’m incredibly proud to have beaten Tiger Woods, as I’ve grown up watching this man,” said 23-year-old John Rahm.
Woods lost all four games in France and now has a 13-21-3 record in his Ryder Cup career.
This is a strange statistic for one of the greatest players of all time, who has won 14 great titles, lagging only behind Jack Nicklaus.
The American team had to fight all weekend to find the streets, with the exception of Patrick Reed, Justin Thomas and Tony Finau, who played high-level golf throughout the tournament.
